---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Dramaturgical Slam — JZ Stafura"
  description="A parody event poster staging Erving Goffman's dramaturgical sociology as a one-night-only pro-wrestling card. Front stage. Back stage. You'll be thrown off the stage."
>
  <div class="back"><a href="/fun/">&#x2190; Fun</a></div>

  <section class="hero">
    <p class="overline">Fun / Parody</p>
    <h1>Dramaturgical Slam</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Front stage! Back stage! You&rsquo;ll be thrown off the stage!</p>
    <div class="meta-row">
      <span class="status status-live">Live</span>
      <div class="links">
        <a href="/dramaturgical-slam.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Enter the Arena &#x2197;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="preview-section">
    <a href="/dramaturgical-slam.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="preview-card">
      <div class="preview-inner">
        <p class="preview-tagline">&ldquo;Two regions enter. One performance leaves. The loser is exposed for who they really are.&rdquo;</p>
        <div class="feature-list">
          <span>The Idealized Self vs. The Self Off Duty</span>
          <span>Front stage / back stage theme toggle</span>
          <span>Sanctioned by Commissioner Erving Goffman</span>
          <span>Civil Inattention, defending since 1963</span>
          <span>Wrestling-poster aesthetic</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="preview-cta">
        Enter the Arena &#x2197;
      </div>
    </a>
    <p class="preview-note">A parody event poster. Opens in a new tab.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="about">
    <h2>About</h2>
    <p>Dramaturgical Slam stages Erving Goffman&rsquo;s <em>The Presentation of Self in Everyday Life</em> (1959) as a one-night-only professional wrestling card. The Idealized Self defends the title against the Self Off Duty; Impression Management and the Performance Team are the reigning tag champions; Civil Inattention has been politely ignored since 1963. The whole arena is contractually looking away.</p>
    <p>Click the stage toggle to flip between front stage (theatrical oxblood and footlight gold) and back stage (cold concrete and worklight). There is, of course, no back stage. The aesthetic is a fight poster. The sociology is real.</p>

    <div class="details-grid">
      <div class="detail-block">
        <h3>Stack</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Vanilla HTML / CSS / JS</li>
          <li>Google Fonts (Alfa Slab One, Oswald, Courier Prime)</li>
          <li>Front/back stage theme switch</li>
          <li>No dependencies</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="detail-block">
        <h3>Disclaimer</h3>
        <p class="detail-desc">No selves were permanently exposed in the making of this card. All disputed decisions are reframed on the spot by the senior official. No refunds on the self.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .back { padding: 1.5rem 0 0; }
  .back a { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  .back a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .overline { font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .hero { padding: 2.5rem 0 2rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); margin-bottom: 2.5rem; }
  .hero h1 { font-size: clamp(1.75rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; letter-spacing: 0.05em; }
  .hero-sub { max-width: 55ch; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; font-style: italic; }
  .meta-row { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1.5rem; }
  .status { font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; padding: 0.2rem 0.55rem; border: 1px solid; }
  .status-live { color: #16a34a; border-color: rgba(22, 163, 74, 0.3); background: rgba(22, 163, 74, 0.05); }
  .links { display: flex; gap: 1.25rem; }
  .links a { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--color-muted); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); padding-bottom: 1px; text-decoration: none; }
  .links a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }

  .preview-section { margin-bottom: 3rem; }

  .preview-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: space-between;
    border: 1px solid #7A1620;
    background: #5A0B12;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: inherit;
    transition: border-color 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
  }

  .preview-card:hover {
    border-color: #E3AE3C;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 24px rgba(227, 174, 60, 0.15);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .preview-inner { padding: 2.5rem 2rem 2rem; }

  .preview-tagline {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-style: italic;
    color: #ECE0C6;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    max-width: 52ch;
  }

  .feature-list { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 0.5rem; }
  .feature-list span {
    font-size: 0.65rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: #DCCBA4;
    border: 1px solid #7A1620;
    padding: 0.25rem 0.65rem;
  }

  .preview-cta {
    padding: 1rem 2rem;
    background: #E3AE3C;
    color: #2F0509;
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .preview-note { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-top: 0.75rem; }

  section.about { padding-bottom: 2rem; }
  .about h2 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: normal; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .about p { color: var(--color-muted); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 1rem; max-width: 65ch; }

  .details-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(200px, 1fr)); gap: 2rem; margin-top: 2rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .detail-block h3 { font-size: 0.75rem; letter-spacing: 0.1em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .detail-block ul { list-style: none; }
  .detail-block li { font-size: 0.875rem; color: var(--color-text); padding: 0.2rem 0; }
  .detail-desc { font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--color-muted); line-height: 1.6; font-style: italic; }
</style>
